revision.text:
'''Abimbola''' (diminutive form as ''"'''Bimbo'''"'') is both a [[Yoruba language|Yoruba]] surname and given name meaning: "born with wealth"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindthename.com/name/abimbola|title=Abimbola|website=Behind the Name}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com.ng/books?id=DSwJCton8GgC&pg=PA63&dq=|page=63|title=Intermediate Yoruba: Language, Culture, Literature, and Religious Beliefs, Part 2|author1=Abraham Ajibade Adeleke Ph. D.|publisher=Trafford Publishing|year=2011|ISBN=978-1-426-9490-98}}</ref>
Notable people with the name include: *[[Abimbola Awoliyi]], Nigerian physician *[[Bola Abimbola]], Nigerian musician *[[Wande Abimbola]] (born 1932), Nigerian academic *[[Abimbola Adelakun]], Nigerian writer *[[Abimbola Alao]] (born 1967), Nigerian writer *[[Abimbola Lagunju]] (born 1960), Nigerian writer
Notable people with the diminutive name form include: *[[Bimbo Manuel]], Nigerian actor *[[Bimbo Oloyede]], Nigerian journalist *[[Bimbo Odukoya]], Nigerian televangelist *[[Bimbo Akintola]], Nigerian actress *[[Bimbo Oshin]], Nigerian actress
