{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2017}} {{BLP sources|date=February 2010}} {{Portuguese name|Schneider|Dick}} {{Infobox model | name = Cintia Dicker | image = | birth_name = Cintia Schneider Dick | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1986|12|06}} | birth_place = [[Campo Bom]], Rio Grande do Sul, Brazil | height = {{height|m=1.78}} | haircolor = Red | eyecolor = Blue | agency = {{Plainlist| * [[Ford Models]] (New York, Los Angeles) * [[Elite Model Management]] (Paris) * [[Why Not Model Management]] (Milan) * [[Storm Model Management]] (London) * Public Image Management (Montreal) * [[Munich Models]] (Munich) * Satoru Japan Inc. (Tokyo)<ref>https://models.com/models/cintia-dicker</ref> }} }} '''Cintia Dicker''' (born '''Cintia Schneider Dick'''<ref>https://www.martinbehrend.com.br/noticias/noticia/id/1048/titulo/modelo-de-campo-bom-estrela-video-de-100-anos-de-beleza-no-brasil-e-indicacao-nao-escapa-de-criticas</ref> on 6 December 1986) is a Brazilian model and swimwear designer.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nymag.com/fashion/models/cdicker/cintiadicker/ |title=Model profile at |publisher=Nymag.com |date=12 June 1986 |accessdate=2011-07-05}}</ref><ref>https://www.si.com/swim-daily/2015/01/15/cintia-dicker-models-newest-dicker-swimwear</ref>
She was born in [[Campo Bom]], Rio Grande do Sul. She has appeared in advertisements for [[Ann Taylor (retail chain)|Ann Taylor]], [[Macy's]], [[L'Oréal]], [[American Eagle Outfitters]], [[Tom Ford]], [[Wildfox Couture]], and [[Yves Saint Laurent (brand)|Yves Saint Laurent]], and in catalogs for [[Victoria's Secret]], [[H&M]], [[Gap (clothing retailer)|Gap]], [[bebe stores]], and [[Lands' End]]. She has been on the covers of French ''[[Marie Claire]]'', ''[[Elle (magazine)|Elle]]'', ''Madame Figaro'' and Brazilian ''[[Vogue magazine|Vogue]]''/''[[Teen Vogue]]'', and was featured in the [[Sports Illustrated Swimsuit Edition]] in 2009, 2010, 2011, 2012 and 2013. Dicker has walked fashion shows including [[Gucci]], [[Anna Sui]], Peter Som, [[Matthew Williamson]], [[Tommy Hilfiger]], [[DSquared²]], [[Lanvin (clothing)|Lanvin]], and [[Dolce & Gabbana]].
Her career modeling and acting for ''[[Sports Illustrated]]'' and other high paying clients has allowed her to support children's charities in Brazil and she also hopes it will allow her to start her own businesses in the future.<ref>http://swimdaily.si.com/2013/03/13/cintia-dicker-25-facts/</ref> She is ranked as one of the 'Top Sexiest" models in the industry.<ref>http://models.com/rankings/ui/TopSexiest-All/3067#3067</ref>
She has described herself as [[spiritualist]].<ref>http://swimdaily.si.com/2013/03/13/cintia-dicker-25-facts/</ref> In 2014, she was given the role of Milita in the Brazilian telenovela [[Meu Pedacinho de Chão]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Após papel sem falas no Fantástico, modelo Cíntia Dicker será filha de Fagundes em novela|url=http://virgula.uol.com.br/diversao/televisao/apos-papel-sem-falas-no-fantastico-modelo-cintia-dicker-sera-filha-de-fagundes-em-novela|accessdate=21 April 2014|newspaper=Vírgula}}</ref> She is a natural redhead.
In 2015 she performed in the 100 Years of Beauty series of the WatchCut Video Youtube Channel, representing her home country Brazil.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Waxman|first1=Olivia B.|title=Watch 100 Years of Brazilian Beauty in Less Than 2 Minutes|url=http://time.com/4094717/100-years-beauty-brazil/|accessdate=16 January 2017|work=TIME.com|date=30 October 2015}}</ref>
