{{BLP primary sources|date=June 2008}}

'''Ma Yue''' ([[Xiao'erjing]]: {{lang|zh-Arab|ﻣَﺎ  ﻳُﻮٔ }}) was born in 1959 to a [[Hui people|Muslim Hui]] family in [[Hebei]], whose association with martial arts goes back six generations.{{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}

As a five-year-old, his father [[Ma Xianda]] took him to train with his grandfather, [[Ma Fengtu]] where he learned his family styles [[Tongbeiquan]], [[Piguaquan]], [[Fanziquan]], [[Bajiquan]], and Cuojiao. At the age of 11, Ma Yue won the [[Xian]] city and [[Shaanxi]] province all-around championships and beat renowned International Wushu champ Zhao Changjun.<ref name="Kungfu Magazine">{{cite web | url = http://ezine.kungfumagazine.com/magazine/article.php?article=244 | title = An interview with Grandmaster Ma Xianda | author = Gigi Oh | accessdate = 2008-10-15}}</ref>

In 1983, he won a four gold awards, placing firsts in fanzi, pigua, short weapon and straight sword.<ref name="Kungfu Magazine"/> Ma Yue has since had a long  career in the martial arts. He is a Chinese National Wushu Champion,{{Citation needed|date=November 2008}} two-time gold medallist{{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}<!-- Of what? --> and a graduate of Wushu University of China.{{Citation needed|date=November 2008}}

