'''Miklós Kovács''' is a [[Hungarian people|Hungarian]] car designer, notable for leading the design team<ref name=Sun>{{cite web|title=Kia plants a Hungarian cee’d|publisher=''[[The Budapest Sun]]''|author=Robin Marshall|url=http://www.budapestsun.com/extras/Motoring_Focus_2007_March.pdf|date=2007-04-19|accessdate=2008-05-19}} {{Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot}}</ref> of the model [[Kia Cee'd]] in [[Frankfurt]], [[Germany]].<ref name=Sun/> 

He graduated in 1995 in [[Pforzheim]], Germany as an automotive designer.<ref>{{cite web|title=Magyar designer tervezte a Kia első európai modelljét |publisher=''HomeGarden'' |language=Hungarian |url=http://www.hg.hu/?hg3=cikk_reszletes&cikk_id=1671 |accessdate=2008-05-19 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071016212321/http://hg.hu/?hg3=cikk_reszletes&cikk_id=1671 |archivedate=2007-10-16 |df= }}</ref> Before working for [[Kia Motors|Kia]], Kovács worked for [[Audi]].<ref>{{cite web|title=A meglepetés erejével |publisher=''Origo'' |language=Hungarian |url=http://www.cegesauto.hu/cikk/80 |date=2006-10-10 |accessdate=2008-05-19 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080527195003/http://www.cegesauto.hu/cikk/80 |archivedate=2008-05-27 |df= }}</ref>

