{{About|the politician|the Irish missionary|Robert Tomlinson|the American musician|Tommy Tomlinson (musician)}} {{Infobox State Senator | image =Tommy Tomlinson.jpg | name = Robert M. Tomlinson | caption = | state_senate = Pennsylvania | district = [[Pennsylvania Senate, District 6|6th]] | term_start = January 3, 1995 | term_end = | predecessor = [[H. Craig Lewis|Craig Lewis]] | successor = | state_house2 = Pennsylvania | district2 = [[Pennsylvania House of Representatives, District 18|18th]] | term_start2 = January 1, 1991 | term_end2 = November 29, 1994 | predecessor2 = [[Edward F. Burns|Ed Burns]] | successor2 = [[Gene DiGirolamo]] | party = [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]] | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1945|12|4|mf=y}} | birth_place = [[Newtown, Bucks County, Pennsylvania|Newtown, Pennsylvania]] | alma_mater = [[West Chester University of Pennsylvania|West Chester University]] | occupation = Funeral Director | residence = [[Bensalem, Pennsylvania]] || religion = [[Presbyterianism|Presbyterian]] | website = http://www.senatortomlinson.com }}
'''Robert M. Tomlinson''' (born December 4, 1945) is a [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]] member of the [[Pennsylvania State Senate]], who has represented the [[Pennsylvania Senate, District 6|6th District]] since 1995. He was previously a member of the [[Pennsylvania House of Representatives]] for the [[Pennsylvania House of Representatives, District 18|18th District]] from 1991 to 1994. He was a director of the [[Bensalem Township School District]] from 1978 to 1990.
==External links== *[http://www.senatortomlinson.com/ Senator Tomlinson] '''official caucus website''' *[http://www.legis.state.pa.us/cfdocs/legis/home/member_information/senate_bio.cfm?id=151 Pennsylvania State Senate - Robert M. Tomlinson] '''official PA Senate website''' *[http://www.votesmart.org/bio.php?can_id=5246 Project Vote Smart - Senator Robert M. "Tommy" Tomlinson (PA)] profile
